'''David Thomas''' (born June 18, 1974 in [[Sangre Grande]]) is a male [[beach volleyball]] player from [[Trinidad and Tobago]].
David made history along with [[Kevin Edwards (beach volleyball)|Kevin Edwards]], becaming the first caribbean team playing in the [[Swatch FIVB World Tour]], the [[Montreal]] Open.<ref>{{cite web 
|url=http://www.fivb.org/EN/Infomedia/WorldVolleyNews/WV_News_06_E_final.pdf
|title=Caribbean pairs make history in Montreal
|author=FIVB
|accessdate=2009-09-07}}</ref>

Playing with the same partner, he earned the 10th place at the [[Beach Volleyball at the 2006 Central American and Caribbean Games|Central American and Caribbean Games]] beach volleyball tournament.<ref>{{cite web 
|url=http://www.norceca.org/XX%20Central%20American_Result_2006_Playa.htm
|title=Final Ranking
|author=NORCECA
|accessdate=2009-09-07}}</ref>

He played in the men's competition at the [[NORCECA Beach Volleyball Circuit 2009]] in [[2009 NORCECA Beach Volleyball Circuit (Guatemala)|Guatemala]] partenering [[Kevin Rivers (beach volleyball)|Kevin Rivers]] when [[Christian Francois]] withdrew from the competition. They finished in the 12th place.<ref>{{cite web 
|url=http://www.fivb.org/EN/BeachVolleyball/viewPressDB.asp?No=12804
|title=Puerto Ricans were perfect on Day One in Guatemala
|author=FIVB
|accessdate=2009-09-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web 
|url=http://www.trinidadexpress.com/index.pl/article_sports?id=161463118
|title=Joseph, Philip back in action
|author=Trinidad Express
|accessdate=2009-09-06}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref>

